            ; -- and each is byte-faithful on a DIFFERENT subset of its four
            ; arms, with no diagnostic in any of the wrong cases: rust and ts
            ; hand back 767 bytes for a 420-byte binary file (U+FFFD for every
            ; invalid byte); go re-encodes 210 as c3 92; go's substring recipe
            ; answers -1 for a byte it read right 2 positions earlier. Their
            ; bands all pass, because their bands are ASCII. equireach (row 807)
            ; names what a byte source COSTS; this names whether it is telling
            ; the truth -- a door that hands back the byte itself. A carrier
            ; needs both, and this stone needed the second one first.
