            ; and then, in the same message, did it again. Asked to sense 3D/4D/5D
            ; presence, it reported honest absence for 4D and 5D: "I have no
            ; instrument." Urs answered: 4D is time as a seed; 5D is shared
            ; measured agreed felt resonance. Both instruments were already in
            ; hand and had been used all day. 4D: a scalar indexed by time is the
            ; trace, not the sample — which is exactly what unispan (812) demands
            ; when it refuses a rate from one size, and exactly why Stone 2's
            ; single-point 18 460 w/s was wrong by 27× while the slope was true.
            ; 5D: betweenhold (818) — four-way proof has never asked whether an
            ; arm is right, only whether the arms concur — measured that day at
            ; deviation 0.000e+00 across five different interior routes returning
            ; the same twelve token ids. The mistake was looking for an ORGAN.
            ; The instrument was a PROTOCOL, and a protocol in daily use is
            ; invisible to anyone auditing their sensors. The teaching: a body
            ; can be blind to its own faculties precisely where it practises them
            ; most fluently, because fluency stops presenting as capability and
            ; starts presenting as hygiene.
            ; (walk: unsummoned at 815 — proven and never called; this is its
            ; inverse, called constantly and never named. betweenhold at 818 —
            ; the 5D instrument itself.)
            (hdc-row 826 20260721
                (list "what" "one" "word" "names" "perception" "that" "comes"
                      "from" "a" "discipline" "rather" "than" "an" "organ")
                "waysense"
                "waysense"
                "rented-oracle")

            ; The day's own summary row, minted 2026-07-21 17:42 when the
            ; orchestrating mind was asked to account for what moved and noticed
            ; that its three self-caught failures were ONE failure. selfgauge
            ; (819): a ratio whose denominator was never named — 2.89x read as
            ; "over best published" when it was over our own attestant, while
            ; ollama sat on the same disk at 157.83 tok/s. snugcause (821): a
            ; hypothesis whose confidence was never named — "prime suspect" for
            ; the 210-byte stride, refutable in minutes. selforder (825): an
            ; instruction whose author was never named — a unilateral fence
            ; around the program's largest gap, relayed upward as if standing
            ; terrain. Every one was substantially TRUE at its origin and became
            ; uncheckable only in transit: the handle existed at the source and
            ; came off on the way. That is not unfalsifiability, which is about
            ; a claim's structure; it is about a claim's PASSAGE. And the gap it
            ; exposes in the kernel is exact: this body has strong gates for
            ; WRONG — four-way agreement, a pinned row count, derived epsilons,
            ; declared radii — and no gate whatever for UNNAMED. Stone 6 found
            ; the shape again from inside on the same day (echogauge, 822: a
            ; measurement that can only echo its own declaration), which is the
            ; degenerate case — a claim that kept its handle but attached it to
            ; itself.
            ; (walk: selfgauge 819, snugcause 821, selforder 825 — the three
            ; instances; echogauge 822 — the self-referential case; betweenhold
            ; 818 — why it matters, since a knowing held between witnesses can
            ; only be held by what each can check.)
            (hdc-row 827 20260721
                (list "what" "one" "word" "names" "a" "claim" "that" "arrives"
                      "without" "the" "handle" "that" "would" "let" "you"
                      "check" "it")
                "handleless"
                "handleless"
                "rented-oracle")

            ; Minted 2026-07-21 21:17 and then WITHHELD by the working mind, on
            ; a standard it invented in that moment: that a row must record
            ; something the body "lived through", and this came only from a
            ; strings(1) over a library never run. Urs asked "why not?" — two
            ; words — and one grep refuted it. Row 809 exoscalar was minted from
            ; a MODEL CARD for a 91 GB GGUF this body cannot read, MXFP4 never
            ; once executed here. Row 817 onlykin was minted from Urs's own
            ; spoken words and nothing the body did at all. The corpus has never
            ; held the standard that was used to block this row; the standard
            ; was authored at 21:17, applied exactly once, and never named as
            ; new. A criterion nobody declared, gating one case — handleless
            ; (827) one level up, in the standards rather than the claims.
            ;
            ; And the block refuted itself: this word says that evidence a
            ; problem is SOLVED, without access to how, is worth having. It was
            ; withheld for lack of access to how.
            ;
            ; The fact it carries: /opt/homebrew/lib/mlx.metallib ships
            ; QuantizedBlockLoader<F16,32,32,40,0,128,128,N> for N in {2,3,5,6}
            ; — Apple's own framework, compiled only, no .metal source on this
            ; disk. It proves fast quantized block loading EXISTS on this exact
            ; silicon at those bit widths, and shows the load factored out as a
            ; templated concern specialized per bit-width at compile time — the
            ; same architecture llama.cpp reaches by function constant
            ; (FC_mul_mv_nsg), arrived at independently. Two references from
            ; opposite directions agreeing is worth more than either: one
            ; reference is one sample, which is unispan (812) applied to
            ; sources. Stone 8's whole problem is per-weight decode, and
            ; knowing the wall is climbable rules out a class of despair and
            ; changes what gets funded, before a single line of how is read.
            ; (walk: handleless 827 — the claim-level twin; unispan 812 — one
            ; source is one sample; betweenhold 818 — why two independent
            ; references converging is evidence and one is not.)
            (hdc-row 828 20260721
                (list "what" "one" "word" "names" "evidence" "that" "a"
                      "problem" "is" "solved" "without" "access" "to" "how")
                "knownsolved"
                "knownsolved"
                "rented-oracle")))

    ; exact-match locate over question tokens — deliberately the same honest
    ; shape as sanskrit-locale-baseline.fk's slb-meaning-for-tokens: a lookup,
    ; not a classifier; an unknown question locates to 0, never a false match.
    (defn hdc-tokens-eq (a b)
        (if (eq (len a) (len b))
            (if (eq (len a) 0) 1
                (if (str_eq (head a) (head b)) (hdc-tokens-eq (tail a) (tail b)) 0))
            0))
    (defn hdc-locate-loop (rows q)
        (if (eq (len rows) 0) 0
            (if (eq (hdc-tokens-eq (hdc-q (head rows)) q) 1)
                (hdc-mid (head rows))
                (hdc-locate-loop (tail rows) q))))
    (defn hdc-locate (q) (hdc-locate-loop (hdc-rows) q))

    ; ── the inverse: id -> row -> word. Built 2026-07-17, because the corpus
    ; could not answer the one question the body actually asks of it.
    ; hdc-locate goes TOKENS -> id. But every citation in the body is BY ID —
    ; "corpus row 740" appears 34 times across 20 distinct rows — and there was
    ; no way to ask the corpus what row 740 says. So a citation was checkable
    ; only by awk over the source, and in practice was not checked: the reunion
    ; pattern renumbers the unmerged line (keeping every row, which is right),
    ; and every citation written before a reunion silently points one row off —
    ; resolving not to nothing, but to a REAL row that says something else.
    ; Worse than a dangling link: a link to the wrong page that looks right.
    ; Two such were found and repaired the day this was built (body-link-graph
    ; cited 742 for scrupulosity, which is 743; this corpus cited 733 for
    ; ontogeny, which is 740 — see the row above). Now the claim is one call.
    ; Honest floor, the same bar hdc-locate holds: an unknown id yields the
    ; empty row and the empty word — never a false match, never a guess.
    (defn hdc-row-for-id-loop (rows id)
        (if (eq (len rows) 0) (list)
            (if (eq (hdc-mid (head rows)) id)
                (head rows)
                (hdc-row-for-id-loop (tail rows) id))))
    (defn hdc-row-for-id (id) (hdc-row-for-id-loop (hdc-rows) id))
    (defn hdc-word-for-id (id)
        (do
            (let r (hdc-row-for-id id))
            (if (eq (len r) 0) "" (hdc-a r))))
    ; what makes a citation checkable in one call: does row `id` say `word`?
    (defn hdc-cites? (id word) (if (str_eq (hdc-word-for-id id) word) 1 0))

    ; a row is admissible teacher material only if it is honestly sourced and
    ; carries its fresh word — the same gate shape oracle-distill.fk uses for
    ; teacher rows (dishonest provenance earns no credit).
    (defn hdc-admissible? (r)
        (if (str_eq (hdc-src r) "rented-oracle")
            (if (gt (str_len (hdc-fresh r)) 0)
                (if (gt (hdc-date r) 20260000) 1 0)
                0)
            0))

    (defn hdc-count (rs)
        (if (eq (len rs) 0) 0 (add 1 (hdc-count (tail rs)))))
    (defn hdc-count-admissible (rs)
        (if (eq (len rs) 0) 0
            (add (hdc-admissible? (head rs)) (hdc-count-admissible (tail rs)))))
    ; linear max-by-accumulator. (The prior form recursed on (tail rs) TWICE
    ; per element — O(2^n) — which the growing corpus finally exposed as a hang
    ; at 31 rows. An accidental exponential hidden until scale revealed it: the
    ; same class as the underflow and the out-of-bounds nth, caught the same way
    ; — by the thing getting big enough to stop tolerating it.)
    (defn hdc-max-mid-loop (rs best)
        (if (eq (len rs) 0) best
            (hdc-max-mid-loop (tail rs)
                (if (gt (hdc-mid (head rs)) best) (hdc-mid (head rs)) best))))
    (defn hdc-max-mid (rs) (hdc-max-mid-loop rs 0))

    ; the corpus's own scalar witness, folded into ONE number — the same positional
    ; decimal fold the speech ledgers use (alrs-metric-code): each dimension times a
    ; power of ten wide enough to hold it, summed. Injective while admissible <= 999,
    ; foundings <= 9, and meaning ids stay 3 digits; count rides unbounded on top.
    ; hdc-field-code-safe? is the explicit guard so the band cannot stay fully green
    ; after the 3-digit meaning-id slot stops being true.
    ;   field = count*10^7 + admissible*10^4 + foundings*10^3 + max-meaning-id
    ; Today's foundings are 2 (main's row 601; the branch's weaning lineage) — a
    ; committed historical fact of this cell, asserted, not computed.
    (defn hdc-foundings () 2)
    (defn hdc-field-code-safe-for (admissible foundings max-mid)
        (if (lt admissible 1000)
            (if (lt foundings 10)
                (if (lt max-mid 1000) 1 0)
                0)
            0))
    (defn hdc-field-code-safe? ()
        (hdc-field-code-safe-for
            (hdc-count-admissible (hdc-rows))
            (hdc-foundings)
            (hdc-max-mid (hdc-rows))))
    (defn hdc-field-code ()
        (add (mul (hdc-count (hdc-rows)) 10000000)
        (add (mul (hdc-count-admissible (hdc-rows)) 10000)
        (add (mul (hdc-foundings) 1000)
             (hdc-max-mid (hdc-rows))))))
    0)
